\section{Big Core Verse} \label{sec:big-core}

\begin{figure}
$$
\begin{array}{rcll}
\multicolumn{4}{l}{\text{\bf Expressions}} \\
|e| & ::= & |x| \vb |k|
    \vb |e_1 `choice` e_2| \vb |def x e|  & \text{Just as in Core} \\
      & \vb & |lam x e|                  & \text{Ordinary lambda} \\
      & \vb & |olam e_1 v_1 v_2|          & \text{Open lambda} \\
      & \vb & |tup (e_1, xdots, e_n)| \\
      & \vb & |e_1 ; e_2| \\
      & \vb & |v = e|                 & \text{Not only on lhs of ``|;|''} \\
      & \vb & |e_1 e_2|                   & \text{Not flattened to values} \\

      & \vb & |x := e|                    & \text{Brings |x| into scope and binds it} \\
      & \vb & |if e_1 then e_2 else e_3|   & \text{Conditional expression} \\
      & \vb & |for(e){b}|                 & \text{Finite loop} \\
      & \vb & |check fx e|                & \text{Effects check} \\
    & \vb & |verify e| \\
    & \vb & |havoc e| \\
    & \vb & |forall x e| \\
    & \vb & |e_1 guard e_2|               & \text{Guard} \\
    & \vb & |assume e|                    & \text{Assumption}
    \\
\multicolumn{4}{l}{\text{\bf Effects}} \\
|fx| & ::= & |succeeds| \vb |decides| \vb |iterates| \vb |fails|
\end{array}
$$
\caption{BigCore Verse expressions} \label{fig:core-verse}
\end{figure}

\Cref{fig:core-verse} gives the Big Core Verse language into which we desugar,
Big Core Verse is slightly larger than the core language of the ICFP 23 paper, but
can very easily be desugared into it.  Specifically:
\begin{itemize}
\item It includes |x := e|.  This means |x=e|, plus an existential for |x| added at the
  top of the enclosing scope.
\item In |if (e_1) then e_2 else e_3| each of the |e_i| has its own scope, but existentials
  at the top of |e_1| also scope over |e_2|.  So |if (x:=f^[0]) { y:=x+1; y*y } else 0| gets turned into
  |if (def x (x==f^[0])) then (def y (y==x+1; y*y)) else 0|.
\item In |for (e_1) {e_2}| both expressions have their own scope, but with top existential in |e_1| scoping over |e_2|.
\end{itemize}


